# HANDOFF.md.template

Copy this file to `HANDOFF.md` at the repo root when Claude.ai is handing off a POC or design to Claude Code.  Fill in the sections.  Claude Code reads this on the first session after handoff and adds an `## Acknowledged` section.

---

# Handoff: [Project / feature name]

**Date**: YYYY-MM-DD
**From**: Claude.ai conversation thread (link or short identifier)
**To**: Claude Code

## What this is

One paragraph: what is being handed off, and why.  Is this a POC graduating to Build?  A new feature within an existing project?  A redesign?

## What's been decided

The conclusions from the POC conversation that should be treated as settled:

(List, with one line each)

## What's been ruled out

Approaches considered and rejected, with the reason.  This prevents Claude Code from re-deriving the same options later.

(List with reasons)

## Data shape

If the POC produced or relies on a specific data shape, describe it here.  Schemas, sample rows, expected ranges, edge cases discovered.

```sql
-- or json, or whatever the canonical shape is
```

## Visual direction

Screenshots, mockups, or component descriptions from the POC.  If an SVG / HTML mockup was produced in Claude.ai, paste it here.

## Open questions

Things that weren't resolved during the POC that Claude Code should ask about or flag when the relevant code is being written:

(List)

## Next concrete steps

The first 3-5 things Claude Code should do.  Be specific enough that they can be executed without further clarification.

1. ____
2. ____
3. ____

## Out of scope for this handoff

Anything that came up but explicitly isn't part of this work yet.

(List)

---

## Acknowledged

(Claude Code adds this section on first read.  Format: date + one-line summary of how Claude Code will proceed.)
